5:
Clear skies, cool breeze...\n
Bring on the lightning, please!
10:
Phew... That takes care of that quest.
Thanks, Nonoa!
15:
Don't thank me! My handy-dandy
umbrella doubles as a weapon!
18:
AND it matches my raincoat
perfectly. I couldn't ask for a better
partner!
27:
Isn't it though? It's a real
cutie-patootie when it's covered in
raindrops!
37:
It's just a passing shower. I'm sure it'll
end shortly.
46:
Nah, it's not too bad. Besides, a little
rain feels good after a workout.
51:
It does, doesn't it?! Glad to see
someone else understands! Now,
let's plippity-plop alon—
55:
Oh, for—will you quick naggin' me?!
Gaaah! I should've KNOWN not to
team up with YOU!
60:
Whoa there, buddies! Time out!
Fighting's bad!
70:
Yup. We've gone on quests together
a bunch of times.
73:
What happened, guys? This
weather's too nice for such frowny
faces.
76:
B-but, Nonoa... This jerk's always
pickin' fights 'bout the smallest
crap... I can't take it!
78:
Ha! Well, neither can I! I'm sick of
seeing you try to brute force your
way out of every problem!
86:
Oh! I get it! You two are like an
umbrella and the rain!
90:
Rain's all drippity-drop without an
umbrella, and you can't hear the
plippity-plop of an umbrella without
rain, right? You need both!
98:
Indeed, they work in perfect
harmony.
106:
H-harmony? With this egghead?! No
way!
109:
Yes way! Once you hear the
plippity-plop, I'm sure you'll
understand!
112:
I know! You just have to share an
umbrella and hear it for yourselves!
115:
Or... Do you really hate each other
that much?
123: Wow! You two were totally in sync!
126: I-I just did what came naturally.
129:
In other words, working in harmony
comes naturally to you.
133:
You know... I'd really like it if we could
all be in a party together again.
Wouldn't you?
136:
*sigh* No way I can say no to our
little buddy.
144:
Thanks! I'm happiest when my
friends are happy too!
148: You remind me of the rain, Nonoa.
152:
Hehe, then you must be the
umbrella, Stella! We work in perfect
harmony!
163:
Err... The meaning behind these
words still eludes me...
168:
Ah, looks like the rain let up. I wonder
if we'll see a rainbow on our way
back.
173:
Oh! I know a great place to see
rainbows!
178:
I would love to see this place with
you, Nonoa.
